---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Electrical Services | Certified Installations in Venezuela"
  description="Professional electrical installations, upgrades, and smart home integration. Certified, safe, and code-compliant work in Valencia, San Diego and Caracas."
  image="/images/electricidad.webp"
  activePage="services"
>
  <header class="article-hero">
    <div class="hero-bg" style="background-image: url('/images/electricidad.webp')"></div>
    <div class="hero-overlay"></div>
    <div class="hero-content">
      <a href="/en/services" class="back-link">← Back to Services</a>
      <span class="article-category">Essential Service</span>
      <h1 class="article-title"><span class="line">Electrical</span><span class="line gold">Services</span></h1>
      <p class="article-excerpt">Safe, certified electrical installations and smart home integration for modern Venezuelan properties.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="article-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="article-body">
        <p>Electrical systems are the backbone of any modern property. Outdated wiring, insufficient capacity, or improper installations create safety hazards and limit what you can do with your space. At ReformaT Venezuela, we bring certified electrical expertise to every project.</p>

        <p>Whether you're renovating a single room or rewiring an entire property, our licensed electricians ensure every installation meets safety standards and supports your current and future needs.</p>

        <img src="/images/electricidad.webp" alt="Professional electrical installation by ReformaT Venezuela" loading="eager" fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" />

        <h2>Common Electrical Issues in Venezuelan Properties</h2>

        <p>Many older properties in Valencia, San Diego, and Caracas have electrical systems that were never designed for modern power demands. Common issues we address:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Insufficient circuits:</strong> Not enough dedicated circuits for appliances, causing frequent breaker trips</li>
          <li><strong>Outdated wiring:</strong> Aluminum or undersized copper wire that poses fire risks</li>
          <li><strong>Ungrounded outlets:</strong> Two-prong outlets that can't safely power modern electronics</li>
          <li><strong>Inadequate panel capacity:</strong> Electrical panels that can't support additional loads</li>
          <li><strong>No GFCI protection:</strong> Missing ground fault protection in wet areas (kitchens, bathrooms)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Our Electrical Services</h2>

        <p><strong>Complete Rewiring:</strong> Replacing outdated wiring with modern copper conductors, adding grounded outlets throughout, and upgrading electrical panels to support contemporary power needs.</p>

        <p><strong>Panel Upgrades:</strong> Installing higher-capacity electrical panels with modern circuit breakers, surge protection, and room for future expansion.</p>

        <p><strong>Dedicated Circuits:</strong> Adding individual circuits for high-draw appliances like air conditioners, electric ranges, dryers, and EV chargers.</p>

        <p><strong>Lighting Design & Installation:</strong> Recessed lighting, track lighting, under-cabinet lighting, and architectural lighting with dimmer controls.</p>

        <p><strong>Smart Home Integration:</strong> Smart switches, automated lighting scenes, voice-controlled outlets, and integration with home automation systems.</p>

        <h2>Smart Home Technology</h2>

        <p>Modern electrical work goes beyond basic wiring. We integrate smart technology that adds convenience, security, and energy efficiency:</p>

        <p><strong>Smart Switches & Dimmers:</strong> Control lights from your phone, set schedules, or use voice commands. Compatible with Alexa, Google Home, and Apple HomeKit.</p>

        <p><strong>Automated Scenes:</strong> Program lighting scenes for different activities—movie night, dinner party, bedtime—with a single tap.</p>

        <p><strong>Motion Sensors:</strong> Lights that turn on automatically when you enter a room and off when you leave, saving energy.</p>

        <p><strong>Smart Outlets:</strong> Monitor energy usage, control devices remotely, and receive alerts if something unusual happens.</p>

        <h2>Safety Standards & Certifications</h2>

        <p>Every electrical installation we perform follows strict safety protocols:</p>

        <ul>
          <li>Proper wire sizing for each circuit load</li>
          <li>GFCI protection in all wet locations</li>
          <li>AFCI protection in bedrooms and living areas</li>
          <li>Proper grounding throughout the system</li>
          <li>Labeling of all circuits in the electrical panel</li>
          <li>Documentation of all work performed</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>The Electrical Renovation Process</h2>

        <p><strong>Assessment:</strong> We evaluate your current electrical system, identify deficiencies, and determine what upgrades are needed.</p>

        <p><strong>Planning:</strong> We create a detailed plan showing all new circuits, outlets, switches, and fixtures, along with load calculations.</p>

        <p><strong>Installation:</strong> Our electricians perform all work with minimal disruption, protecting your property and cleaning up daily.</p>

        <p><strong>Testing & Certification:</strong> Every circuit is tested for proper function and safety before we consider the job complete.</p>

        <h2>Why Choose ReformaT for Electrical Work?</h2>

        <ul>
          <li>Licensed, certified electricians on staff</li>
          <li>Knowledge of Venezuelan electrical codes and standards</li>
          <li>Experience with both residential and commercial properties</li>
          <li>Smart home integration expertise</li>
          <li>Comprehensive warranties on all electrical work</li>
          <li>Clean, professional installations</li>
          <li>English-speaking project management available</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Need electrical work?</strong> <a href="/en/contact">Schedule your free consultation</a> and receive a detailed electrical assessment and quote.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="cta-wrapper">
      <h2 class="cta-title">Ready to Upgrade Your Electrical System?</h2>
      <p class="cta-text">Schedule a free consultation with our certified electricians.</p>
      <a href="/en/contact" class="btn-premium btn-primary-premium">
        <span class="btn-content">Request a Quote</span>
        <span class="btn-border"></span>
        <span class="btn-shine"></span>
        <span class="btn-arrow">→</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .article-hero { position: relative; min-height: 80vh; display: flex; align-items: flex-end; justify-content: center; text-align: center; color: var(--white); overflow: hidden; padding-top: 140px; padding-bottom: 80px; }
  .hero-bg { position: absolute; inset: 0; background-size: cover; background-position: center; z-index: 1; }
  .hero-overlay { position: absolute; inset: 0; background: linear-gradient(to top, rgba(0,0,0,0.95) 0%, rgba(0,0,0,0.4) 60%, rgba(0,0,0,0.2) 100%); z-index: 2; }
  .hero-content { position: relative; z-index: 3; max-width: 900px; padding: 0 20px; }
  .article-category { display: inline-block; background: rgba(201,169,97,0.2); border: 1px solid var(--gold); color: var(--gold); padding: 8px 20px; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 2px; margin-bottom: 25px; backdrop-filter: blur(10px); }
  .article-title { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 5rem); font-weight: 400; margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 1.1; }
  .article-title .line { display: block; }
  .article-excerpt { font-size: 1.3rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto; line-height: 1.6; font-weight: 400; }
  .back-link { display: inline-block; color: var(--gold); font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 20px; transition: 0.3s; text-decoration: none; }
  .back-link:hover { color: var(--gold-light); }
  .article-section { padding: 80px 0; background: var(--white); }
  .article-body { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text); }
  .article-body h2 { font-size: 2.5rem; margin: 3rem 0 1.5rem; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 500; }
  .article-body h3 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem; color: var(--text); font-weight: 500; }
  .article-body p { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; font-weight: 400; }
  .article-body a { color: var(--gold); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gold); }
  .article-body ul, .article-body ol { margin: 1.5rem 0 1.5rem 2rem; }
  .article-body li { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-weight: 400; }
  .article-body img { border-radius: 12px; margin: 2.5rem 0; box-shadow: 0 15px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.08); width: 100%; }
  .article-body > p:first-of-type::first-letter { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 4.5rem; font-weight: 600; float: left; line-height: 0.75; margin-right: 0.15em; color: var(--gold); margin-top: 8px; }
  .cta-section { background: var(--bg); color: var(--white); text-align: center; padding: 110px 24px; width: 100%; }
  .cta-wrapper { max-width: 950px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; }
  .cta-title { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 3.6rem); font-weight: 400; margin-bottom: 24px; line-height: 1.15; color: var(--white); text-align: center; width: 100%; }
  .cta-text { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85); max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto 45px; font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.7; font-weight: 400; text-align: center; width: 100%; }
  .cta-section .btn-premium { padding: 20px 55px; font-size: 0.9rem; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .article-hero { min-height: 70vh; padding-top: 120px; padding-bottom: 60px; }
    .article-title { font-size: clamp(2rem, 8vw, 3.5rem); }
    .article-excerpt { font-size: 1.15rem; }
    .article-body { font-size: 1.15rem; }
    .article-body h2 { font-size: 2rem; }
    .article-body h3 { font-size: 1.5rem; }
    .cta-section { padding: 90px 20px; }
    .cta-title { font-size: 2.2rem; }
    .cta-text { font-size: 1.15rem; }
  }
</style>